CSC '94 STUDENT POSTER SESSION COMPETITION

The student poster sessions offer students a chance to meet others
in their field as well as provide employers with an opportunity to
meet the top students from the schools represented.  Students
whose abstracts are nominated by their departments and accepted
by the committee will present their research in poster session
format.  Competition will be conducted in two categories, graduate
and undergraduate.  Prizes will be awarded on the basis of peer
review to take place during the conference.  Each school may
nominate a maximum of three student papers, limited to two in any
one category.  The application deadline is January 7, 1994.
Notification of acceptance will be no later than January 21, 1994.
For further details and instructions for submitting, contact:

Drs. Kenneth and Sally Goldman
CSC '94 Poster Competition
Department of Computer Science
Washington University, Campus Box 1045
St. Louis, MO 63130-4899
ACM-POSTERS@CS.WUSTL.EDU
(314) 935-6160


THE 1994 ACM SCHOLASTIC PROGRAMMING CONTEST

Winners of regional contests will meet at CSC '94 to compete in the
programming contest finals. All colleges and universities are
encouraged to enter their regional competition. For additional
information, contact Lisa Ernst at ACM Headquarters by calling
212-626-()513 or ftp to anonymous acm.org ftp site for the latest
contest information.


THE 24TH ACM INTERNATIONAL COMPUTER CHESS CHAMPIONSHIP

will begin on March 6. The Championship will be a five round,
Swiss-style event, with rounds played during the day on Sunday
and on the following evenings. Games will be played at a speed of
4() moves per side for the first two hours of play and 20 for any
additional hours.  Prizes will be awarded after the final game.

